ated_by\":\"1\",\"created_on\":\"2019-12-06 14:15:52\",\"modified_by\":\"16\",\"modified_on\":\"2020-01-09 15:29:11\",\"title\":\"Art Grant Writing Seminar & Workshop\",\"url\":\"art-grant-writing-seminar-and-workshop\",\"start_date\":\"2017-01-16 13:00:00\",\"end_date\":\"2020-01-09 15:27:36\",\"cover\":\"10\",\"short_description\":\"A crash course that will give you the main perspective and tools to make a competitive grant application. In this seminar you will be instructed step by step through the narrative structure of a grant application. You will learn formulating your project description and artist statement. Additionally, you will explore the ways of finding the suitable German and International application calls for your project\\/artwork.\",\"external_participants\":null,\"links\":null,\"description\":\"<p>We are happy to host Berlin Art Grant Clinic in Lacuna Lab with the:<\\/p><p><strong>ART GRANT WRITING SEMINAR and WORKSHOP: 16, 17, 24 &amp; 25 January<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Early bird registration date: 12 January 2017<\\/p><p><strong>GRANT DIAGNOSIS SEMINAR (16-17 January)<\\/strong><\\/p><p> This is simply a crash course that will give you the main perspective and tools to make a competitive grant application. In this seminar you will be instructed step by step through the narrative structure of a grant application. You will learn formulating your project description and artist statement. Additionally, you will explore the ways of finding the suitable German and International application calls for your project\\/artwork.<\\/p><p><strong>Working topics include:<\\/strong><\\/p><p> Day #1: On Funding Bodies<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Understanding Funding Bodies<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Decision process in funding application evaluations<\\/p><p> \\u2013 List of grant givers<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Places to find grant givers<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Getting over your writing blockage<\\/p><p>Day #2: On Applications<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Structure of funding applications<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Creating a project description<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Writing your artist statement<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Key elements, tips and tricks for a successful application<\\/p><ul><li>20 mins. one-to-one consultancy with each participant on a particular project.<\\/li><\\/ul><p><strong>OPERATION WORKSHOP (24-25 January)<\\/strong><\\/p><p> This is a hands-on grant writing workshop for artists, artistic projects and applications for residency programmes. The workshop aims at preparing you to submit better applications to the up-coming open calls. It is for applicants who want to develop their existing grant writing skills. Throughout Module #1 you will have to the opportunity to learn how to create a timeline and an efficient budget, and in Module #2 you will be able to exchange ideas and views with your peers, polish your application, and get equipped for your upcoming proposals.<\\/p><p><strong>Working topics include:<\\/strong><\\/p><p> Day #1: Time, Budget, Tips and Tricks<\\/p><p> \\u2013 A focused timeline<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Focused and realistic budgeting<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Tips and tricks to avoid emergency expenditure<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Working with a sample application<\\/p><p>Day #2: Hands-on Application Operation<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Requirements for a good proposal<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Making yourself a strong applicant<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Enriching and polishing your content<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Working on your application \\u2013 peer evaluation<\\/p><p>FOR MORE INFO on content, fees &amp; registration:<\\/p><p> <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/artgrantclinic.org\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">http:\\/\\/artgrantclinic.org\\/<\\/a><\\/p><p> <a href=\\\"mailto:berlingrantclinic@gmail.com\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">berlingrantclinic@gmail.com<\\/a><\\/p>\"}','{\"end_date\":\"2020-01-09 15:27:36\",\"description\":\"<p>We are happy to host Berlin Art Grant Clinic in Lacuna Lab with the:<\\/p><p><strong>ART GRANT WRITING SEMINAR and WORKSHOP: 16, 17, 24 &amp; 25 January<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Early bird registration date: 12 January 2017<\\/p><p><strong>GRANT DIAGNOSIS SEMINAR (16-17 January)<\\/strong><\\/p><p> This is simply a crash course that will give you the main perspective and tools to make a competitive grant application. In this seminar you will be instructed step by step through the narrative structure of a grant application. You will learn formulating your project description and artist statement. Additionally, you will explore the ways of finding the suitable German and International application calls for your project\\/artwork.<\\/p><p><strong>Working topics include:<\\/strong><\\/p><p> Day #1: On Funding Bodies<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Understanding Funding Bodies<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Decision process in funding application evaluations<\\/p><p> \\u2013 List of grant givers<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Places to find grant givers<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Getting over your writing blockage<\\/p><p>Day #2: On Applications<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Structure of funding applications<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Creating a project description<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Writing your artist statement<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Key elements, tips and tricks for a successful application<\\/p><ul><li>20 mins. one-to-one consultancy with each participant on a particular project.<\\/li><\\/ul><p><strong>OPERATION WORKSHOP (24-25 January)<\\/strong><\\/p><p> This is a hands-on grant writing workshop for artists, artistic projects and applications for residency programmes. The workshop aims at preparing you to submit better applications to the up-coming open calls. It is for applicants who want to develop their existing grant writing skills. Throughout Module #1 you will have to the opportunity to learn how to create a timeline and an efficient budget, and in Module #2 you will be able to exchange ideas and views with your peers, polish your application, and get equipped for your upcoming proposals.<\\/p><p><strong>Working topics include:<\\/strong><\\/p><p> Day #1: Time, Budget, Tips and Tricks<\\/p><p> \\u2013 A focused timeline<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Focused and realistic budgeting<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Tips and tricks to avoid emergency expenditure<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Working with a sample application<\\/p><p>Day #2: Hands-on Application Operation<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Requirements for a good proposal<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Making yourself a strong applicant<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Enriching and polishing your content<\\/p><p> \\u2013 Working on your application \\u2013 peer evaluation<\\/p><p>FOR MORE INFO on content, fees &amp; registration:<\\/p><p> <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/artgrantclinic.org\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">http:\\/\\/artgrantclinic.org\\/<\\/a><\\/p><p> <a href=\\\"mailto:berlingrantclinic@gmail.com\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">berlingrantclinic@gmail.com<\\/a><\\/p>\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1306,1377,'events','5','{\"id\":\"5\",\"status\":\"published\",\"sort\":null,\"created_by\":\"1\",\"created_on\":\"2019-12-06 14:17:33\",\"modified_by\":\"16\",\"modified_on\":\"2020-01-09 15:30:06\",\"title\":\"Serious Sparkles. An Inquiry into Artificial Stupidity\",\"url\":\"serious-sparkles-an-inquiry-into-artificial-stupidity\",\"start_date\":\"2017-02-10 13:00:00\",\"end_date\":\"2020-01-09 15:29:16\",\"cover\":\"29\",\"short_description\":\"An Inquiry into Artificial Stupidity explores our current state of willful ignorance in the post-fact era. In this state reality and fabrication blur into one another and sparkly treats provide welcome distractions. Visitors are invited to explore an elusive physical and digital snapshot of our ever-shifting collaborative activities across a range of tools and methods such as robotics, audio-visual performance, generative art and machine learning.\",\"external_participants\":null,\"links\":null,\"description\":\"<p>Lacuna Lab presents a two-day exhibition of interactive artworks, with a performance and talk on each evening. Serious Sparkles.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><strong>Exhibition 10.02 \\u2013 11.02.<\\/strong><\\/p><p>An Inquiry into Artificial Stupidity explores our current state of willful ignorance in the post-fact era. In this state reality and fabrication blur into one another and sparkly treats provide welcome distractions. Visitors are invited to explore an elusive physical and digital snapshot of our ever-shifting collaborative activities across a range of tools and methods such as robotics, audio-visual performance, generative art and machine learning.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><strong>Participating Artists<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Nayeli Vega, Thomas Heidtmann, Sarah Hermanutz, Marcel Schwittlick, Ramin Soleymani, Jemma Woolmore, Gene Kogan, Peter Kolski, Nenad Popov, James Kneafsey, Thomas O\\u2019Reilly<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><strong>Performance 10.02.<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Sarah Hermanutz and Nenad Popov will debut their new audio-visual performance collaboration. In \\u201cLive Decomposition\\u201d, inspiration is drawn from the sights, sounds, and textures of wetlands, where life and death mingle in swampy, sparkling layers of sensation.<\\/p><p>20:00 - Nenad Popov &amp; Sarah Hermanutz - Live Decomposition<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><strong>Talks 11.02.<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Lacuna Lab presents an evening of talks with Yvonne Reiners, curator, and founder of Performing Encounters, and Nick Houde, PhD candidate at the EGS and research associate for the Technosphere project at HKW. Themes in the exhibit \\u201cSerious Sparkles\\u201c will be considered from the perspective of each speaker\\u2019s own curatorial and philosophical research. Reiners will discuss self-empowerment and human-machine interactions within the current media environment of fake news and memes, while Houde shares his analysis about the future of meaning and general intelligence in cultural production in relation to science, art, and fiction.<\\/p><p>19:00 - Yvonne Reiners (Performing Encounters)<\\/p><p>19:45 - Nick Houde (PhD EGS, Researcher at HKW)<\\/p><p>Opening hours<\\/p><p>Fri 10th from 18:00 to 23:00 pm<\\/p><p>Sat 11th from 13:00 to 23:00 pm<\\/p><p>Lacuna Lab<\\/p><p>Paul-Lincke-Ufer 44A<\\/p><p>2.HH 1.OG<\\/p><p>10999 Berlin<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Lacuna Lab is about collaboration. We mix logic and beauty to create interactive works for us and for you. We are driven by imagination, playfulness, and experimentation. We love partnering with others on projects and collaborations, and sharing what we learn through public exhibitions, classes, and workshops.<\\/p><p>This exhibition is part of the official Transmediale 2017 Vorspiel <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vorspiel.berlin\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/vorspiel.berlin\\/<\\/a><\\/p>\"}','{\"end_date\":\"2020-01-09 15:29:16\",\"description\":\"<p>Lacuna Lab presents a two-day exhibition of interactive artworks, with a performance and talk on each evening. Serious Sparkles.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><strong>Exhibition 10.02 \\u2013 11.02.<\\/strong><\\/p><p>An Inquiry into Artificial Stupidity explores our current state of willful ignorance in the post-fact era. In this state reality and fabrication blur into one another and sparkly treats provide welcome distractions. Visitors are invited to explore an elusive physical and digital snapshot of our ever-shifting collaborative activities across a range of tools and methods such as robotics, audio-visual performance, generative art and machine learning.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><strong>Participating Artists<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Nayeli Vega, Thomas Heidtmann, Sarah Hermanutz, Marcel Schwittlick, Ramin Soleymani, Jemma Woolmore, Gene Kogan, Peter Kolski, Nenad Popov, James Kneafsey, Thomas O\\u2019Reilly<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><strong>Performance 10.02.<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Sarah Hermanutz and Nenad Popov will debut their new audio-visual performance collaboration. In \\u201cLive Decomposition\\u201d, inspiration is drawn from the sights, sounds, and textures of wetlands, where life and death mingle in swampy, sparkling layers of sensation.<\\/p><p>20:00 - Nenad Popov &amp; Sarah Hermanutz - Live Decomposition<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><strong>Talks 11.02.<\\/strong><