e audience is invited to participate actively in a collective ritual without leaving their home.<\\/p><p>In order to take part, you will need a smartphone or tablet running with a frontal camera and the zoom.us app installed. During the event, you will be given simple instructions to move through your apartment, that you have to follow. Please be aware that the event will be recorded and published and by partaking, you agree to the distribution of your image.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Mit freundlicher Unterst\\u00fctzung des Fonds Darstellende K\\u00fcnste aus Mitteln der Beauftragten der Bundesregierung f\\u00fcr Kultur und Medien im Rahmen von NEUSTART KULTUR \\/\\/ In Kooperation mit PATHOS M\\u00fcnchen<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Links:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.pathosmuenchen.de\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals?fbclid=IwAR01tBqmAc12WsW7naWMAwJAQm5SeGzJhGE6LgS3xhQICpbZLCLBxRaq2Ms\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" style=\\\"background-color: transparent;\\\">https:\\/\\/www.pathosmuenchen.de\\/...\\/remote-rules-and-rituals<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"gallery\":null}','{\"status\":\"draft\",\"description\":\"<p>Paul Wiersbiski (Lacuna Lab, Berlin) will investigate how the rituals of theatre can be used to portray the ritualism of spiritual machines. How do we use them to make predictions about an uncertain future?<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>His aim is to develop a format in between digitality and theatre. The audience is invited to participate actively in a collective ritual without leaving their home.<\\/p><p>In order to take part, you will need a smartphone or tablet running with a frontal camera and the zoom.us app installed. During the event, you will be given simple instructions to move through your apartment, that you have to follow. Please be aware that the event will be recorded and published and by partaking, you agree to the distribution of your image.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Mit freundlicher Unterst\\u00fctzung des Fonds Darstellende K\\u00fcnste aus Mitteln der Beauftragten der Bundesregierung f\\u00fcr Kultur und Medien im Rahmen von NEUSTART KULTUR \\/\\/ In Kooperation mit PATHOS M\\u00fcnchen<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Links:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.pathosmuenchen.de\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals?fbclid=IwAR01tBqmAc12WsW7naWMAwJAQm5SeGzJhGE6LgS3xhQICpbZLCLBxRaq2Ms\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" style=\\\"background-color: transparent;\\\">https:\\/\\/www.pathosmuenchen.de\\/...\\/remote-rules-and-rituals<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"short_description\":\"Paul Wiersbiski will investigate how the rituals of theatre can be used to portray the ritualism of spiritual machines. How do we use them to make predictions about an uncertain future?\",\"start_date\":\"2021-01-29 19:00:00\",\"end_date\":\"2021-01-29 20:00:00\",\"title\":\"Remote Rules and Rituals\",\"url\":\"remote-rules-and-rituals\",\"cover\":81,\"links\":[{\"title\":\"Free Tickets\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.pathosmuenchen.de\\/...\\/remote-rules-and-rituals\"},{\"title\":\"Facebook Event\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/events\\/3865279546882156\\/\"}]}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1888,2071,'events_directus_users','12','{\"id\":\"12\",\"events_id\":\"46\",\"directus_users_id\":\"17\"}','{\"directus_users_id\":17,\"events_id\":\"46\"}','events',NULL,1),(1889,2072,'events_locations','21','{\"id\":\"21\",\"events_id\":\"46\",\"locations_id\":\"5\"}','{\"locations_id\":5,\"events_id\":\"46\"}','events',NULL,1),(1890,2073,'events','44','{\"id\":\"44\",\"status\":\"published\",\"sort\":null,\"created_by\":\"17\",\"created_on\":\"2020-07-24 11:36:24\",\"modified_by\":\"14\",\"modified_on\":\"2021-01-22 11:43:21\",\"title\":\"Spaced Out in Outer Space\",\"url\":\"spaced-out-in-outer-space\",\"start_date\":\"2020-11-01 00:00:00\",\"end_date\":null,\"cover\":\"76\",\"short_description\":\"Lacuna Lab is transformed into a film set, in which we will develop and document a concert performance. We mix live elements with pre-produced recordings and visual impressions from Kreuzberg.\",\"external_participants\":[{\"name\":\"Behrang Karimi\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/bertholdpott.com\\/artists\\/behrang-karimi\"}],\"links\":null,\"description\":\"<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/469247091\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/469247091<\\/a><\\/p><p>(Passwort: SpacePlace)<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em style=\\\"color: rgb(120, 144, 156);\\\">We\\u2019re always glad when they come. But also to see them go. The things that remain, the arches and ornaments, tell us of a life that has been lived. Single shards spell out eternity. Jars and vessels are libraries and witnesses all at once: the outlines of eternal travelers who never arrive, but shouldn\\u2019t be impeded. Decisions should only be made when one is aware of various possibilities. Retreat into one\\u2019s own existence. Dilute one\\u2019s identity. \\u2018I\\u2019 is only a construction, too. Swim. Be water my friend. So limpid as to provide a large area for the phantoms and projections of others. Transparent bodies. A heart of glass. Back in the days, people never got old enough to get cancer. Procedures. The representation of death as sickness. The metaphysical order of things. An understanding that living beings in the world are compositions standing side by side, tightly bound enough to make it through the day, and that in spite of everything they are of this earth, in life and death. And this way of being an \\u2018earthling\\u2019 is a kind of counterpoint to the transcendentalism of philosophy, science and politics, as well as all the other, different regimes that involve a commitment to deathlessness. The spider weaves the world.<\\/em><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>In our project \\u201cSpaced Out in Outer Space\\u201d we will examine the history of the balance in cybernetics and biology and its influence on our contemporary conception of nature and society. We are interested in the question of the extent to which notions of \\u201cpure\\u201d nature, immortality and space travel have always been a fantasy in western science and art to escape a faulty existence and to change it instead of accepting its limits.&nbsp;<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>For this purpose, Paul Wiersbinski will create stories and shoot videos to examine narration itself as a political tool and to talk about what future communities might look like. Based on these narratives, Behrang Karimi will produce drawings and paintings.&nbsp;Our goal is to tell a story that is big enough and yet open to talk about current doomsday fantasies. As Donna Haraway says, \\\"It depends on what thoughts think about thoughts.\\\"&nbsp;<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Both artists have worked together several times, including with earlier funding from the NRW Kunststiftung for the exhibition \\u201cDumb Pigs Smart Pigs\\u201d about the possibility of a utopian society of pigs and most recently at the Schauspiel K\\u00f6ln as part of the scenic dance installation \\u201cFlakon\\u201d together with Mara Tsironi.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>funded by \\/ gef\\u00f6rdert aus Mitteln der Projektf\\u00f6rderung des Bezirks Friedrichshain-Kreuzberg<\\/p>\",\"gallery\":null}','{\"short_description\":\"Lacuna Lab is transformed into a film set, in which we will develop and document a concert performance. We mix live elements with pre-produced recordings and visual impressions from Kreuzberg.\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1891,2074,'events','46','{\"id\":\"46\",\"status\":\"published\",\"sort\":null,\"created_by\":\"14\",\"created_on\":\"2021-01-22 11:41:35\",\"modified_by\":\"14\",\"modified_on\":\"2021-01-22 11:50:02\",\"title\":\"Remote Rules and Rituals\",\"url\":\"remote-rules-and-rituals\",\"start_date\":\"2021-01-29 19:00:00\",\"end_date\":\"2021-01-29 20:00:00\",\"cover\":\"81\",\"short_description\":\"Paul Wiersbiski will investigate how the rituals of theatre can be used to portray the ritualism of spiritual machines. How do we use them to make predictions about an uncertain future?\",\"external_participants\":null,\"links\":[{\"title\":\"Free T