/p><p>The event is part of Lacuna Lab\'s event series:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/transmediale-vorspiel-2021-or-scattered-partners\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\\\">Transmediale Vorspiel 2021 | Scattered Partners<\\/a><\\/p>\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1932,2124,'events','45','{\"id\":\"45\",\"status\":\"published\",\"sort\":null,\"created_by\":\"3\",\"created_on\":\"2021-01-16 13:47:33\",\"modified_by\":\"14\",\"modified_on\":\"2021-01-26 10:39:11\",\"title\":\"Transmediale Vorspiel 2021 | Scattered Partners\",\"url\":\"transmediale-vorspiel-2021-or-scattered-partners\",\"start_date\":\"2021-01-15 00:00:00\",\"end_date\":\"2021-03-31 23:59:59\",\"cover\":\"78\",\"short_description\":\"In the midst of the global pandemic caused by covid-19, Transmediale celebrates the Vorspiel 2021, and due to the lockdown conditions, Lacuna Lab proposes an entirely digital program.\",\"external_participants\":[{\"name\":\"\",\"url\":null}],\"links\":null,\"description\":\"<p>In the midst of the global pandemic caused by covid-19, Transmediale celebrates the Vorspiel 2021, and due to the lockdown conditions, Lacuna Lab proposes an entirely digital program.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>28 January 7 pm to 30 March 11 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna | <strong>Snapshot<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna present a series of film interviews that reflect a momentary snapshot in the life of Lacuna Lab and its members. These interviews take a record of the artworks presented by the members during Vorspiel along with their individual backgrounds, influences, and points of view.<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/snapshot\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/snapshot<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>29 January 7 pm to 29 January 8 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Paul Wiersbiski | <strong>Remote Rules and Rituals<\\/strong><\\/p><p>The project investigates how the rituals of theatre can be used to portray the ritualism of spiritual machines. How do we use them to make predictions about an uncertain future?<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>19 February 5 pm to <\\/em><em style=\\\"color: rgb(120, 144, 156);\\\">19 February <\\/em><em>6 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Fara Peluso | <strong>Comprehensive Thinkers for a Post-Anthropocene<\\/strong><\\/p><p>A talk by the artist-designer Fara Peluso showing how art and design can be mediators between science and the public to build a collective memory.<\\/p><p>More info: <\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>25 February 7 pm to 28 February 11 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Nayeli Vega Vargas, Thomas Heidtmann, Ambika Joshi | <strong>K(not) a Conversation<\\/strong><\\/p><p>K(not) a Conversation&nbsp;is an installation exploring the concepts of artificial intelligence, creativity and labour. Inspired by ancient indigenous communication systems of Quipu knots, it instigates a communication and reflection process through the use of knots and AI systems.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>More info: coming soon<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>25 March 7 pm to 25 March 8 pm (tbc)<\\/em><\\/p><p>Thomas Heidtmann | <strong>slideedge.io \\u2013 digital inauguration<\\/strong><\\/p><p>slideedge.io constitutes an artistic framework which unites interactive sculptural installations with a dynamically generated virtual layer. During Vorspiel a digital prototype is presented to introduce the project to the public.<\\/p><p>More info: coming soon<\\/p>\",\"gallery\":null}','{\"description\":\"<p>In the midst of the global pandemic caused by covid-19, Transmediale celebrates the Vorspiel 2021, and due to the lockdown conditions, Lacuna Lab proposes an entirely digital program.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>28 January 7 pm to 30 March 11 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna | <strong>Snapshot<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna present a series of film interviews that reflect a momentary snapshot in the life of Lacuna Lab and its members. These interviews take a record of the artworks presented by the members during Vorspiel along with their individual backgrounds, influences, and points of view.<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/snapshot\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/snapshot<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>29 January 7 pm to 29 January 8 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Paul Wiersbiski | <strong>Remote Rules and Rituals<\\/strong><\\/p><p>The project investigates how the rituals of theatre can be used to portray the ritualism of spiritual machines. How do we use them to make predictions about an uncertain future?<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>19 February 5 pm to <\\/em><em style=\\\"color: rgb(120, 144, 156);\\\">19 February <\\/em><em>6 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Fara Peluso | <strong>Comprehensive Thinkers for a Post-Anthropocene<\\/strong><\\/p><p>A talk by the artist-designer Fara Peluso showing how art and design can be mediators between science and the public to build a collective memory.<\\/p><p>More info: <\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>25 February 7 pm to 28 February 11 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Nayeli Vega Vargas, Thomas Heidtmann, Ambika Joshi | <strong>K(not) a Conversation<\\/strong><\\/p><p>K(not) a Conversation&nbsp;is an installation exploring the concepts of artificial intelligence, creativity and labour. Inspired by ancient indigenous communication systems of Quipu knots, it instigates a communication and reflection process through the use of knots and AI systems.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>More info: coming soon<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>25 March 7 pm to 25 March 8 pm (tbc)<\\/em><\\/p><p>Thomas Heidtmann | <strong>slideedge.io \\u2013 digital inauguration<\\/strong><\\/p><p>slideedge.io constitutes an artistic framework which unites interactive sculptural installations with a dynamically generated virtual layer. During Vorspiel a digital prototype is presented to introduce the project to the public.<\\/p><p>More info: coming soon<\\/p>\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(1933,2125,'directus_files','85','{\"id\":\"85\",\"storage\":\"local\",\"filename\":\"ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"title\":\"Ctfpa Cover\",\"type\":\"image\\/jpeg\",\"uploaded_by\":\"14\",\"uploaded_on\":\"2021-01-26 09:41:08\",\"charset\":\"binary\",\"filesize\":\"582046\",\"width\":\"3333\",\"height\":\"2500\",\"duration\":\"0\",\"embed\":null,\"folder\":null,\"description\":\"\",\"location\":\"\",\"tags\":[],\"checksum\":\"68656786b63953f447a1b6c31392ee99\",\"metadata\":null,\"data\":{\"full_url\":\"https:\\/\\/api.lacunalab.org\\/uploads\\/lacuna\\/originals\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"url\":\"\\/uploads\\/lacuna\\/originals\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"thumbnails\":[{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/api.lacunalab.org\\/thumbnail\\/_\\/1200\\/1200\\/crop\\/good\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"relative_url\":\"\\/thumbnail\\/_\\/1200\\/1200\\/crop\\/good\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"dimension\":\"1200x1200\",\"width\":1200,\"height\":1200},{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/api.lacunalab.org\\/thumbnail\\/_\\/1400\\/1400\\/crop\\/good\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"relative_url\":\"\\/thumbnail\\/_\\/1400\\/1400\\/crop\\/good\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"dimension\":\"1400x1400\",\"width\":1400,\"height\":1400},{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/api.lacunalab.org\\/thumbnail\\/_\\/1800\\/1800\\/crop\\/good\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"relative_url\":\"\\/thumbnail\\/_\\/1800\\/1800\\/crop\\/good\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"dimension\":\"1800x1800\",\"width\":1800,\"height\":1800},{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/api.lacunalab.org\\/thumbnail\\/_\\/2000\\/2000\\/crop\\/good\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"relative_url\":\"\\/thumbnail\\/_\\/2000\\/2000\\/crop\\/good\\/ctfpa-cover.jpg\",\"dimension\":\"2000x2000\",\"width\":2000,\"height\":2000},{\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/api.lacunalab.or