,2233,'events','50','{\"id\":\"50\",\"status\":\"published\",\"sort\":null,\"created_by\":\"14\",\"created_on\":\"2021-02-08 12:56:20\",\"modified_by\":\"14\",\"modified_on\":\"2021-02-21 12:01:21\",\"title\":\"K(not) a Conversation \\u2013 Communication through knots and AI systems\",\"url\":\"knot-a-conversation-communication-through-knots-and-ai-systems\",\"start_date\":\"2021-02-25 19:00:00\",\"end_date\":\"2021-02-28 23:00:00\",\"cover\":\"89\",\"short_description\":\"K(not) a Conversation is an installation exploring the concepts of artificial intelligence, creativity and labour. Inspired by ancient indigenous communication systems of Quipu knots, it instigates a communication and reflection process through the use of knots and AI systems. \",\"external_participants\":[{\"name\":\"Ambika Joshi\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/computationalmama.xyz\\/\"}],\"links\":[{\"title\":\"Facebook Event\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/events\\/914070462679494\"},{\"title\":\"knotaconversation.art\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/knotaconversation.art\"}],\"description\":\"<p>K(not) a Conversation is an installation exploring the concepts of artificial intelligence, creativity and labour. Inspired by ancient indigenous communication systems of Quipu knots, it instigates a communication and reflection process through the use of knots and AI systems.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>For transmediale \\/ Vorspiel &amp; CTM artists Nayeli Vega Vargas, Thomas Heidtmann, Ambika Joshi present the second version of the project. It completes the <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/befantastic.in\\/2020\\/11\\/16\\/knot-a-conversation\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">original concept<\\/a> developed during the CoLab Fellowship by introducing an enhanced digital version and by showcasing a first physical sculpture prototype.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>Visit <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/knotaconversation.art\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">knotaconversation.art<\\/a> to find out more about the project.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>The event is part of Lacuna Lab\'s event series: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/transmediale-vorspiel-2021-or-scattered-partners\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Transmediale Vorspiel 2021 | Scattered Partners<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>Access to OpenAI\\u2019s GPT-3 kindly supported by Dara, a global community for change-makers &amp; cultural professionals. Join the network here: <\\/em><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.dara.network\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><em>https:\\/\\/www.dara.network\\/<\\/em><\\/a><\\/p><p><em>Special thanks to <\\/em><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/curiouswala.com\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><em>Hasan S.<\\/em><\\/a><em> and <\\/em><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/ophelia.game\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><em>Anushka Trivedi<\\/em><\\/a><em> for additional help with the GPT-3 implementation.<\\/em><\\/p><p><em>Nayeli Vega Vargas is supported by Elsa Neumann Scholarship of the State of Berlin.<\\/em><\\/p><p><em>Thomas Heidtmann wird gef\\u00f6rdert durch die Senatsverwaltung f\\u00fcr Kultur und Europa des Landes Berlin.<\\/em><\\/p>\",\"gallery\":null}','{\"title\":\"K(not) a Conversation \\u2013 Communication through knots and AI systems\",\"url\":\"knot-a-conversation-communication-through-knots-and-ai-systems\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(2027,2234,'events','45','{\"id\":\"45\",\"status\":\"published\",\"sort\":null,\"created_by\":\"3\",\"created_on\":\"2021-01-16 13:47:33\",\"modified_by\":\"14\",\"modified_on\":\"2021-02-21 12:03:13\",\"title\":\"Transmediale Vorspiel 2021 | Scattered Partners\",\"url\":\"transmediale-vorspiel-2021-or-scattered-partners\",\"start_date\":\"2021-01-15 00:00:00\",\"end_date\":\"2021-03-31 23:59:59\",\"cover\":\"78\",\"short_description\":\"In the midst of the global pandemic caused by covid-19, Transmediale celebrates the Vorspiel 2021, and due to the lockdown conditions, Lacuna Lab proposes an entirely digital program.\",\"external_participants\":[{\"name\":\"Ambika Joshi\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/computationalmama.xyz\\/\"}],\"links\":[{\"title\":\"Facebook Event\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/events\\/846522596199943\"}],\"description\":\"<p>In the midst of the global pandemic caused by covid-19, Transmediale celebrates the Vorspiel 2021, and due to the lockdown conditions, Lacuna Lab proposes an entirely digital program.<\\/p><p>Artists: Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna, Nayeli Vega Vargas, Sarah Hermanutz, Thomas Heidtmann, Paul Wiersbinski, Fara Peluso, Mart\\u00edn Nadal, Ambika Joshi<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>26 January 12 am to 31 March 11 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna | <strong>Snapshot<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna present a series of film interviews that reflect a momentary snapshot in the life of Lacuna Lab and its members. These interviews take a record of the artworks presented by the members during Vorspiel along with their individual backgrounds, influences, and points of view.<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/snapshot\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/snapshot<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>29 January 7 pm to 29 January 8 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Paul Wiersbiski | <strong>Remote Rules and Rituals<\\/strong><\\/p><p>The project investigates how the rituals of theatre can be used to portray the ritualism of spiritual machines. How do we use them to make predictions about an uncertain future?<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>16 February 8 pm to 16 February 9 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Sarah Hermanutz | <strong>Mind Blind Pathetic Sublime: Explaining The Pathetic Sublime to An Axolotl Audience<\\/strong><\\/p><p>This lecture is a live-streamed Zoom performance from an unvisitable installation. Seeking comfort, escape, and clarity the artist will use whatever tools are at her disposal to finally help axolotls to understand the Pathetic Sublime.<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/mind-blind-pathetic-sublime-explaining-the-pathetic-sublime-to-an-axolotl-audience\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/mind-blind-pathetic-sublime-explaining-the-pathetic-sublime-to-an-axolotl-audience<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>19 February 5 pm to 19 February 6 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Fara Peluso | <strong>Comprehensive Thinkers for a Post-Anthropocene<\\/strong><\\/p><p>A talk by the artist-designer Fara Peluso showing how art and design can be mediators between science and the public to build a collective memory.<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/comprehensive-thinkers-for-a-post-anthropocene\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/comprehensive-thinkers-for-a-post-anthropocene<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>25 February 7 pm to 28 February 11 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Nayeli Vega Vargas, Thomas Heidtmann, Ambika Joshi | <strong>K(not) a Conversation \\u2013 Communication through knots and AI systems<\\/strong><\\/p><p>K(not) a Conversation&nbsp;is an installation exploring the concepts of artificial intelligence, creativity and labour. Inspired by ancient indigenous communication systems of Quipu knots, it instigates a communication and reflection process through the use of knots and AI systems.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>More info: https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/knot-a-conversation-communication-through-knots-and-ai-systems<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>18 March 7 pm to 18 March 8 pm (tbc)<\\/em><\\/p><p>Thomas Heidtmann | <strong>slideedge.io \\u2013 digital inauguration<\\/strong><\\/p><p>slideedge.io constitutes an artistic framework that unites interactive sculptural installations with a dynamically generated virtual layer. During Vorspiel a digital prototype is presented to introduce the project to the public.<\\/p><p>More info: coming soon<\\/p>\",\"gallery\":null}','{\"description\":\"<p>In the midst of the global pandemic caused by covid-19, Transmediale celebrates the Vorspiel 2021, and due to the lockdown conditions, Lacuna Lab proposes an entirely digital program.<\\/p><p>Artists: Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna, Nayeli Vega Vargas, Sarah Hermanutz, Thomas Heidtmann, Paul Wiersbinski, Fara Peluso, Mart\\u00edn Nadal, Ambika Joshi<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>26 January 12 am to 31 March 11 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna | <strong>Snapshot<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Nu\\u00f1o de la Serna present a series of film interviews that reflect a momentary snapshot in the life of Lacuna Lab and its members. These interviews take a record of the artworks presented by the members during Vorspiel along with their individual backgrounds, influences, and points of view.<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/snapshot\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/snapshot<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>29 January 7 pm to 29 January 8 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Paul Wiersbiski | <strong>Remote Rules and Rituals<\\/strong><\\/p><p>The project investigates how the rituals of theatre can be used to portray the ritualism of spiritual machines. How do we use them to make predictions about an uncertain future?<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/remote-rules-and-rituals<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>16 February 8 pm to 16 February 9 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Sarah Hermanutz | <strong>Mind Blind Pathetic Sublime: Explaining The Pathetic Sublime to An Axolotl Audience<\\/strong><\\/p><p>This lecture is a live-streamed Zoom performance from an unvisitable installation. Seeking comfort, escape, and clarity the artist will use whatever tools are at her disposal to finally help axolotls to understand the Pathetic Sublime.<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/mind-blind-pathetic-sublime-explaining-the-pathetic-sublime-to-an-axolotl-audience\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/mind-blind-pathetic-sublime-explaining-the-pathetic-sublime-to-an-axolotl-audience<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>19 February 5 pm to 19 February 6 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Fara Peluso | <strong>Comprehensive Thinkers for a Post-Anthropocene<\\/strong><\\/p><p>A talk by the artist-designer Fara Peluso showing how art and design can be mediators between science and the public to build a collective memory.<\\/p><p>More info: <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/comprehensive-thinkers-for-a-post-anthropocene\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/comprehensive-thinkers-for-a-post-anthropocene<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>25 February 7 pm to 28 February 11 pm<\\/em><\\/p><p>Nayeli Vega Vargas, Thomas Heidtmann, Ambika Joshi | <strong>K(not) a Conversation \\u2013 Communication through knots and AI systems<\\/strong><\\/p><p>K(not) a Conversation&nbsp;is an installation exploring the concepts of artificial intelligence, creativity and labour. Inspired by ancient indigenous communication systems of Quipu knots, it instigates a communication and reflection process through the use of knots and AI systems.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>More info: https:\\/\\/lacunalab.org\\/events\\/knot-a-conversation-communication-through-knots-and-ai-systems<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><em>18 March 7 pm to 18 March 8 pm (tbc)<\\/em><\\/p><p>Thomas Heidtmann | <strong>slideedge.io \\u2013 digital inauguration<\\/strong><\\/p><p>slideedge.io constitutes an artistic framework that unites interactive sculptural installations with a dynamically generated virtual layer. During Vorspiel a digital prototype is presented to introduce the project to the public.<\\/p><p>More info: coming soon<\\/p>\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(2028,2237,'events','47','{\"id\":\"47\",\"status\":\"published\",\"sort\":null,\"created_by\":\"14\",\"created_on\":\"2021-01-25 17:43:39\",\"modified_by\":\"3\",\"modified_on\":\"2021-02-22 12:37:17\",\"