INSERT INTO `directus_users` VALUES (1,'active','Gilbert','Sinnott ( Autr )','g@sinnott.cc','$2y$10$3RFeUwdh1kLuv9JkOFpsBOwJxzFdtqErkm6Yvmhj644WmquRDK4bK',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,94,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-18 04:26:36','/collections/directus_users/+',NULL,'<p>Gilbert Sinnott is an electronic media artist and designer.&nbsp;Hailing from Bristol (UK), he now lives and works in Berlin. Under the moniker Autr he performs and exhibits video works combining hacked and repurposed analogue video equipment with digital methods, tools and self-built software.<br></p>','[{\"title\":\"autr.tv\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/autr.tv\"},{\"title\":\"@autr.tv\",\"url\":\"www.instagram.com\\/autr.tv\"}]','gilbert-sinnott','member'),(2,'active','Saki','Hibino','saki@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$hRsHSUuhc9BeLwdYCMemnOr9QhqlRyrDF/hRw8TTH7N9iNMTdFa.S',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,47,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'26d8597a-10b6-4601-842f-e6bff779e871',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/sakihibino.com\\/\"}]','saki-hibino','member'),(3,'active','Nuño','de la Serna','nuno@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$5jw54vCnPBB6M3Ykezn99OaMCxumYiumHn18Q0CqwAPqfg23qnC8C',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,79,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-02-22 14:05:28','/users','0820dfc9-d296-4451-97e3-1476706fc18c','<p>Nuño de la Serna Vicente is a Spanish Berlin-based media artist.</p><p>Born in Soria, Spain in 1992 he grew up constantly moving between cities. This nomadic lifestyle gave him an eclectic character that influences his work.</p><p>Mixing multiple art disciplines with inventive ways of using technology, Nuño tries to improve the coexistence between humans and technology. His creative process acknowledges the importance of the fair use of resources and free access to information. Nuño creates artworks that are born from fundamental innocent curiosity and resonate with complex contemporary issues.<br></p><p>In 2017, he started his career as self employed artist and focused on building communities for independent artists, free thinkers, engineers and scientists. He is currently member co-organizer of the Creative Code Berlin and founder of the / niːviːili / art platform.<br></p><p>Self-taught artist and engineer, Nuño acknowledges the importance of the free access to information and supports the free software movement.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>','[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/action-io.com\\/\"},{\"title\":\"Instagram\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/action.io\"},{\"title\":\"Creative Code Berlin\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/creativecode.berlin\\/\"},{\"title\":\"\\/ ni\\u02d0vi\\u02d0ili \\/\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/niviili.com\\/\"}]','nuno','member'),(4,'invited','Magdalena','Kovarik','magdalena@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$y9pL2XwJvQzB8phDjzzdJ.BrWaR11xfKWBQN5BSl8QBe4E9yz9vNC',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,49,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'e2e6bbf6-be83-4edc-a7a7-75e07b7e9a24',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.magdalenakovarik.com\\/\"}]','magdalina-kovarik','alumni'),(5,'invited','Joao ','Fonseca','joao@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$a9GEP7GNCHBBEh67nKpGZuQtIFJims0F3egEGivsPJ0oGOzt.MtsW',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,50,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'3f7f0e8b-20b2-4df3-a830-23aca787e200',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/joaofonseca.cc\\/\"}]','joao-fonseca','alumni'),(6,'invited','Koki ','Ikiburo','koki@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$CZAPldRmhSx.6QLMRyV5I.a5BrBlgrUVsI8GX2IQXNr77/DQdsqii',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,61,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'712f16bf-ec58-40ab-932a-f79afb79e5bc',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.koki-ibukuro.com\\/\"}]','koki-ikiburo','alumni'),(7,'invited','Merlin','Carter','merlin@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$Nrw7EbretA1E1bmLYlNj/uHhOIgy36WCH0qeNS9.73.HLJgEUD1R6',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,51,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-01-16 19:01:34','/settings','27634470-1129-4631-ac9b-adbc20528dba',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/merlincarter.com\\/\"}]','merlin-carter','alumni'),(8,'invited','Sahar','Homami','sahar@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$dCynGtQeSowcN/ZUK7Efu.b1PXuHTofntzCGKlvkYgVl5l0Z3KDn6',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,52,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'11c32318-12ac-4b2b-b193-0bb9d943943b',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.saharhomami.com\\/\"}]','sahar-homami','alumni'),(9,'invited','Jemma','Woolmore','jemma@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$3KHisuCIbm1bT5niN9skHOFs/KxZxbgdWinVESJTkuNgE2PSLnDzW',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,67,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-01-16 18:13:45','/users','a0611ca5-f7ec-468d-9c9e-bc780df0de68','<p>Blurring the boundaries between real and virtual, Jemma’s work explores the spatial and emotional possibilities of light and image in performative environments.</p><p>Hailing from New Zealand where she completed her Fine Arts degree, Jemma has made a unique path, weaving between the visual arts and electronic music scenes.  Spanning audio-visual performance, installation and bespoke visual and sculptural design, her work shows a strong sensitivity for combining light, sound and structure.</p><p>Often working in immersive and large scale multi-screen environments,  she carefully crafts abstract textural landscapes  that fluctuate ambiguously in scale between the micro and macro, responding intuitively with sound and environment.</p><p>Inspired by naturally occurring patterns, and imbued with a sense of science fiction otherworldliness, Jemma’s work uses recurring symbols to interrogate the fragile boundary between Utopia and Dystopia.  </p><p>In Berlin Jemma is a curator for Scope Sessions Artist Talks and Media Salon and works as a member of Lacuna Lab.</p>','[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/jemmawoolmore.com\\/\"}]','jemma-woolmore','alumni'),(10,'active','Nayeli','Vega','nayeli@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$KSYZp7ESmhaB0IFF4WBS/.x3T0MqCVv.fMfxKStneVbaD7RFJNJdq',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,95,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-02-22 14:13:34','/users/10','77e4e3c6-8be2-4d81-bf78-077560646d0b',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/yokoiki.com\\/\"},{\"title\":\"Instagram\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/yokoikilab\\/\"},{\"title\":null,\"url\":null}]','nayeli-vega','member'),(11,'active','Nenad','Popov','nenad@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$I19nKc4yeEPJ69YtP0Cmh.qRUWzF9ivlkIwsr9noCABeuZQBos4Eq',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,55,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'2f7bf047-daff-41d9-87bc-f505d092a706',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/morphogenesis.eu\\/\"}]','nenad-popov','member'),(12,'active','Sarah','Hermanutz','sarah@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$5BfKhFWiYXjWpRvZi6LKJOS0lvaz.NZX7neMnRVG7c2pMyWBqiobO',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,56,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'3a06082d-0cf8-4a73-aa88-f09399ef0a3a',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/sarahhermanutz.com\\/\"}]','sarah-hermanutz','member'),(13,'deleted','Petja','Ivanova','petja@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$9MnV7dOGHVDeKntIILxF..eqLoauI7uATh7ljMMmBwkXVFLA5csxK',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'4fa30562-a92f-4535-98ba-125d8e975bb2',NULL,NULL,'petja-ivanova','member'),(14,'active','Thomas','Heidtmann','thomas@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$MtEhHkIywY4t/tSOyN6Gu.2ectBbkXSJAMjzKJyNqjnSKtwIXOm5K',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,70,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-18 09:14:50','/collections/directus_users','71992392-cb14-40d2-ad99-7d9051197ecd','<p>Thomas Heidtmann is a Berlin-based media artist, studied at the Berlin University of the Arts. He works at the intersection of art, science and technology. Since 2015 he has been a co-founder and board member of Lacuna Lab e.V. As founder of the space art initiative SPARTH (since 2017) and its community SPARTHabitat (since 2018), he investigates and promotes space art activities. His works have been presented internationally and examine forms of exploration, collaboration, and space.</p>','[{\"title\":\"www.thomasheidtmann.de\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.thomasheidtmann.de\\/\"},{\"title\":\"www.sparth.org\",\"url\":\"www.sparth.org\"}]','thomas-heidtmann','member'),(15,'active','Nahum','_','nahum@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$2/FmP9nPNtmldBVtkullceuh/iEQuZjjl1gI47qCxqabWaWfy3eYG',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,58,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-01-03 11:24:17','/collections/directus_users','4057af3e-6b00-499f-91d6-7654df28df10',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/nahum.xyz\\/\"}]','nahum','member'),(16,'invited','Vincent ','Van Uffelen','vincent@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$/Ne07fP0LmVW0Jvm/LhIj.l5ktfGlSxMQXafDuhJCRlnAEa.O5rVK',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,63,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-01-09 18:01:30','/users','3064b8ea-090a-429c-a83a-8313e5c45644',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/vincentvanuffelen.com\\/\"}]','vincent-van-uffelen','alumni'),(17,'active','Paul','Wiersbinski','paul@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$1kp7oTQcrk3aR8OgbxvBQehZ/bWwjRO9bI8KJCmrD7mkKWvn9IRqu',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,60,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-01-27 10:38:38','/users','de0fe233-5769-4487-97e6-5fae60d24199','<p>I studied video art with Mark Leckey and Douglas Gordon at the Städelschule in Frankfurt (Main) and currently live and work in Berlin.</p><p>My projects are conducted in between the lines of art, science and technology, touching discourses on artificial intelligence, entomology or cybernetics and referring to the history of performance and video art, as well as utilising notions of jest and improvisation. Often I construct technical prototypes, which are tried out by the public and go through various phases of continuous development.</p><p>My work has been presented in intl. Exhibitions: “RECORD &gt; AGAIN!”, ZKM Karlsruhe&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: var(--white); letter-spacing: 0.01em;\">(2009), “The indifference of Wisdom”, NURTUREart New York City (2013), “Risk Society”, MOCA Taipei (2013),&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color: var(--white); letter-spacing: 0.01em;\">“Showcase”, SPACE London (2018), “Offline Browser“, Hong-Gah Museum Taiwan (2018-2019), “Datami”, BOZAR&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color: var(--white); letter-spacing: 0.01em;\">Bruessels (2019-2020) / festivals &amp;screenings: SALT Beyoğlu Istanbul (2012), Luminato Festival Toronto (2014),&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color: var(--white); letter-spacing: 0.01em;\">European Media Arts Festival, Osnabrück (2010, 2014, 2015, 2017), “IN/OUT“ Festival of the National Gallery&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color: var(--white); letter-spacing: 0.01em;\">Amman (2019) and received various prices and grands, such as support from Hauptstadtkulturfonds Berlin.</span></p><p>I hold lectures and presentations: “Push your art” Palais de Tokyo, Paris (2013), “Art in the Age of Earthquakes” Martin-Gropius-Bau, Berlin (2016), “Re:publica” Berlin (2019), “The Whole Life Academy“ Haus der Kulturen der Welt, Berlin (2021-22) and worked as an EU-expert for “Resonances III“ at the Joint Research Centre (JRC) in Ispra (2018-2021).</p>','[{\"title\":\"1. Link to AI-Project\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/resonances.jrc.ec.europa.eu\\/blog\\/portrait-ai-young-cyber-oracle\"},{\"title\":\"2. Interview on Augmented Reality Performance \\\"Mortal Toys\\\"\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.goethe.de\\/ins\\/gb\\/en\\/kul\\/mag\\/21144258.html\"},{\"title\":\"3. Publication \\\"Doing Absolutely Nothing\\\"\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/circadian.co\\/product\\/doing-absolutely-nothing\"},{\"title\":null,\"url\":null},{\"title\":null,\"url\":null},{\"title\":null,\"url\":null}]','paul-wiersbinski','member'),(18,'active','Sé','Sneaky','something@something.com','$2y$10$mruiNpqIsDUqgbkSlSd3cujF7oP4b7Wri3df8z68LeydWtulyhSsm',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'9b6f03d1-6144-4153-9027-1516848c49f2',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"SeSneaky.com\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/sesneaky.com\"}]','se-sneaky','alumni'),(19,'active','Mickey','van Olst','info@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$tdGtQIQfGAcX/GK.Ys836umCB0bSCfBIJinEuGZWqsZiApv6skG72',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-01-08 18:57:28','/collections','9b86e5bc-f8db-4f10-806a-8e726a67f75b',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Personal Website\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/mickeyvanolst.com\\/\"}]','mickey-van-olst','alumni'),(21,'active','Gene','Kogan','gene@something.com','$2y$10$ZJEqaBMx7cviOEsd0V1Pxuk4bcuWL778T.qvc.wzCZ6HaFmhmJMlC',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'e1353c9b-f361-464b-ac6f-32096dfcb5a4',NULL,NULL,'gene-kogan','alumni'),(22,'active','Bidisha','Das','bids@somethinbg.com','$2y$10$Q/NB/WcOB43eMPHLdvNr2.FNcdd6wzX2i7OvyDJPjoXRam7XrjBd.',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'efc1fa4c-bd6e-4f53-9fcb-761f3b01fbb7',NULL,NULL,'bidisha-das','residency'),(23,'active','Cyborgs','e.V.','hello@cyborgs.cc','$2y$10$fsYl5Ho8s3IypjN9/ch/Re2DMr246JxDxGU9lSpQi6dtSBePQwrdq',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,72,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'a0886394-a5a0-4859-b157-ce33cf9dbb1f',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"cyborgs.cc\"}]','cyborgs','alumni'),(24,'active','Fara','Peluso','fara@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$UdiFXLrQvSISf.NbznZIAuzyXMVw9oJOmtU6mI9dmNXPqmcbj8/o.',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,96,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-10 11:12:58','/users','cbde2e0b-b4b1-47df-9e25-325d234e387e','<p>Fara Peluso is a Berlin based artist - designer. She is graduated in industrial design at University Architecture \'La Sapienza\' in Rome and as graphic designer. Through the speculative research she plays how to connect the human being with nature, living organisms and biological processes in a deeper relationship. Constantly researching and taking inspiration from elements present in Nature, she believes that it’s a great Strategy for Design. The relationship between the human being and its environment is observed and the concept that we are the most important living organisms on earth is cancelled. Fara Peluso wants to contribute to raise critical questions considering it a role belonging to artists and designers, she asks how the design of new tools trough a speculative methodology can be applied in this way. Fictional artifacts that tell the story of a possible future scenario about the quality our lifes, attitudes and choices. As artist designer with a strong interest on Biology, Fara Peluso pursues her deep research on algae taking constantly inspiration from them, experimenting and understanding how to work with them inside the Art and Design field. Her work is focused on both the material and the procedural aspects, investigating through a speculative methodology possible closer relationships between human beings and algae.</p>','[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.farapeluso.com\\/site\\/works\\/\"}]','fara','member'),(25,'active','Carlotta ','Piccinini','carlotta.piccinini@gmail.com','$2y$10$60Dynw9musNSDQXpv2U2bOmxH5rjSzU2ANJFt1SyTIe/LPCzL1EPe',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'6774e05f-f714-4fdc-8877-2e199c102b27',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.carlottapiccinini.com\"}]','carlotta','member'),(26,'active','Britani ','Samperi','britanisamperi@gmail.com','$2y$10$SOmckjSZq8hoG6BBlwE3/OAuSfjz7SKzDSmpx/O/aJQXQDUfq0eIC',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'6e4abbda-97d1-4478-8d78-435e23bc624d',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Email\",\"url\":\"mailto:britanisamperi@gmail.com\"}]','britani','member'),(27,'active','Scott','Sinclair','scott@lacunalab.org','$2y$10$lvFC.bhnYZkXOjbVdxyfHe1PrOfkBThtSH6th5EYsegxPRU.cKop.',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,77,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-10 11:03:38','/users','2abf6480-97f9-40a0-8a5b-17a87d5b4d7b',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Website\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/halftheory.com\"},{\"title\":null,\"url\":null}]','scott','member'),(28,'active','Sophia ','Lee','sophiechka@googlemail.com','$2y$10$39NkyWga2Hzbv8nhN8vic.rk2K03X4i5o8zkwigkW7AqAsJKbnDX.',NULL,'Europe/Berlin','en-US',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'5da354e8-96be-45f6-81d2-0ab9eeb779eb',NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Email\",\"url\":\"mailto:sophiechka@googlemail.com\"}]','sophia','member'),(29,'active','Martín ','Nadal','martin.nadal@gmail.com','$2y$10$3o5WTJskqeAZQK7F